The paper focuses on the use of non-linear activation functions in neural networks for classification tasks, which is a common topic in the field of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also conducts an empirical analysis on the MNIST classification task, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of different weight initialisation schemes, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper may also fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL) as it discusses the use of neural networks for classification tasks.
